{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/blag/emacs-the-good-parts","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>This was originally titled \"The emacs workflows that make putting up with a\nmostly single-threaded text editor UI that can be slow and freeze worth it\";\nsuffice it to say I have a love-hate relationship with emacs<sup id=\"fnref-1\"><a href=\"#fn-1\" class=\"footnote-ref\">1</a></sup>.</p>\n\n      <div class=\"footnotes\">\n        <hr/>\n        <ol >\n    \n    <li class=\"footnote-list-item\" id=\"fn-1\" >\n          \n        <p class=\"footnote-paragraph\" style=\"display:inline; \">I hope that after <a href=\"https://github.com/remacs/remacs\">remacs</a> is fully</p>\n      <a href=\"#fnref-1\" class=\"footnote-backref\" style=\"display:inline;text-decoration: none;\">\n        â†©\n      </a>\n    \n      </li>\n      \n    </ol></div>\n<p>ported to rust, they feel comfortable adding to the user experience of the\ndefault installation; I realize that this would be very difficult to design in a\nway that wouldn't add maintenance overhead to the elisp portion of the\nfork though, and the majority of the editor is implemented in elisp.</p>\n<h2 id=\"magit\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#magit\" aria-label=\"magit permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>magit</h2>\n<h3 id=\"show-off-magit-status-a-little\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#show-off-magit-status-a-little\" aria-label=\"show off magit status a little permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>show off magit-status a little</h3>\n<h4 id=\"jump-to-line-in-source-code\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#jump-to-line-in-source-code\" aria-label=\"jump to line in source code permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>jump to line in source code</h4>\n<h4 id=\"stage-and-unstage-a-chunk-quickly\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#stage-and-unstage-a-chunk-quickly\" aria-label=\"stage and unstage a chunk quickly permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>stage and unstage a chunk quickly</h4>\n<h4 id=\"highlight-and-unstage-a-targeted-bit-of-code\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#highlight-and-unstage-a-targeted-bit-of-code\" aria-label=\"highlight and unstage a targeted bit of code permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>highlight and unstage a targeted bit of code</h4>\n<h4 id=\"jump-to-log-and-view-a-specific-commits-diff\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#jump-to-log-and-view-a-specific-commits-diff\" aria-label=\"jump to log and view a specific commits diff permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>jump to log and view a specific commit's diff</h4>\n<ol>\n<li>you can visit that commit, of course, but let's not be so tediously thorough as to actually do it</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"staging-and-committing\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#staging-and-committing\" aria-label=\"staging and committing permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>staging and committing</h3>\n<h4 id=\"stage-some-lines-visually\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#stage-some-lines-visually\" aria-label=\"stage some lines visually permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>stage some lines visually</h4>\n<h4 id=\"look-there-in-the-menu-instant-fixup\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#look-there-in-the-menu-instant-fixup\" aria-label=\"look there in the menu instant fixup permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>look, there in the menu: INSTANT FIXUP!</h4>\n<p>Oh, it's so good. Especially if you've done a deep dive on git, you may know\nabout fixup commits, but interactively choosing the commit from a lineup instead\nof the whole run-commit-with-obscure-flag song and dance is a big step up in\nconvenience and intuitiveness.</p>\n<h3 id=\"when-it-comes-time-to-write-your-commit-youre-in-your-full-editor\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#when-it-comes-time-to-write-your-commit-youre-in-your-full-editor\" aria-label=\"when it comes time to write your commit youre in your full editor permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>when it comes time to write your commit, you're in your full editor</h3>\n<p>you can split a screen, copy-paste some code from the source, etc</p>\n<h2 id=\"dired\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#dired\" aria-label=\"dired permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>dired</h2>\n<p>dired intends to replace the following shell commands directly:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>ls</li>\n<li>cd</li>\n<li>opening some file in $EDITOR</li>\n<li>mkdir</li>\n<li>rm</li>\n</ul>\n<p>See how it looks like <code class=\"language-text\">ls -l</code> output? It literally is <code class=\"language-text\">ls -l</code> output, and that's\nuseful: you can edit a variable to change the options passed to <code class=\"language-text\">ls</code>, if you so\ndesire, and you can test run your selections by running <code class=\"language-text\">ls -l</code> [<sup>1</sup>].</p>\n<p>[1]: That's the thing about emacs: its integration with the underlying operating\nsystem is just as deep as a shell environments', and it shares a lot of\ndetails with one because of it. But it's different: it evolved in parallel\nwith the modern implementations of a shell, though unix shells are much older.\nHow much time you've invested learning a shell first will shape how you learn\nand use emacs.</p>\n<p>dired also has one super-power:</p>\n<h3 id=\"wdired\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#wdired\" aria-label=\"wdired permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>wdired</h3>\n<p>This level of functionality, where you have a super mario version of a specific\nmode with its own keybindings, is why you have to be down with <code class=\"language-text\">M-x</code> and looking\nup commands by name to get the most out of emacs: it would be insane to have to\nremember some cryptic keyboard shortcut for something so dired-specific, because\ndired is just one mode out of many. To get to this level of functionality in a\nsane way, the emacs tradeoff is to be willing to memorize a name or two, as with\na codebase, in order to use it. (but that's the point: emacs <em>is</em> a codebase).\nSo:</p>\n<h4 id=\"m-x-wdired--use-autocomplete--hit-enter\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#m-x-wdired--use-autocomplete--hit-enter\" aria-label=\"m x wdired  use autocomplete  hit enter permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><code class=\"language-text\">M-x wdired</code> + use autocomplete + hit enter</h4>\n<p>If you want to type out the full command like a psycho, it's <code class=\"language-text\">M-x\nwdired-change-to-wdired-mode</code>, but why would you? Of course, you have to\nmanually set up autocomplete, because a blank emacs install is optimized for\nmaintainers, not for beginners. This is a design antipattern, though I\nunderstand the appeal.</p>\n<h4 id=\"make-a-executable-file-in-wdired-its-just-changing-one-character\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#make-a-executable-file-in-wdired-its-just-changing-one-character\" aria-label=\"make a executable file in wdired its just changing one character permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>make a executable file in wdired; it's just changing one character</h4>\n<p>afterward run that file with <code class=\"language-text\">M-!</code></p>","frontmatter":{"date":"2019-12-02 06:34:30 UTC","path":"/blag/emacs-the-good-parts","title":"emacs: the good parts"}}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}